  "comments" : [ {
    "name" : "Comment 1",
    "text" : "Vensim Model Reader"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 2",
    "text" : "Welcome to"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 3",
    "text" : "the"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 4",
    "text" : "Click here to for a quick tour of the Vensim Model Reader"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 5",
    "text" : "The Vensim Model Reader is a freely distributable program that allows Vensim users to publish their models."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 6",
    "text" : "With it you can open, explore and simulate models that have been developed by others."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 7",
    "text" : "Click on one of the options below to find out how to:"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 8",
    "text" : "Open a model"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 9",
    "text" : "Simulate a model"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 10",
    "text" : "Run a game with a model"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 11",
    "text" : "Print and Copy"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 12",
    "text" : "Make a graph"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 13",
    "text" : "Overview"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 14",
    "text" : "Get more info about Vensim"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 15",
    "text" : "Back to Overview"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 16",
    "text" : "This is what a model usually looks like"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 17",
    "text" : "How to Simulate"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 18",
    "text" : "WIPPER"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 19",
    "text" : "c advertising spending,0,2e+008,500000"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 20",
    "text" : "Advertising Spending ($/year)"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 21",
    "text" : "obsolescence time,0.5,10,0.1"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 22",
    "text" : "Product Lifetime (years)"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 23",
    "text" : "1.  To simulate a model first click on the \"SyntheSim Icon\" in the toolbar"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 24",
    "text" : "2. Then make changes to model assumptions by dragging sliders or clicking on highlighted names"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 25",
    "text" : "3.  Then click on the running person to the right of the name - you can name your run whatever you want"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 26",
    "text" : "Back to Overview"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 27",
    "text" : "or"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 28",
    "text" : "Start Gaming"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 29",
    "text" : "WIPPER"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 30",
    "text" : "advertising spending,0,2e+008,500000"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 31",
    "text" : "Advertising Spending ($/year)"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 32",
    "text" : "1.  To start gaming click on the game icon (like a chess board)"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 33",
    "text" : "2.  When you do that some variables may highlight or there may be sliders like the one above"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 34",
    "text" : "3.  Drag the slider or click on a highlighted variable and then click on the forward arrow button in the tool bar"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 35",
    "text" : "4.  You can make more changes and continue to move forward.  You can also look at graphs and tables anytime"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 36",
    "text" : "Back to Overview"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 37",
    "text" : "Opening a model"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 38",
    "text" : "To open a model just use the File>Open Model command or click on the opening folder icon in the toolbar."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 39",
    "text" : "A file selection dialog will appear.  Select the model you want to work with and click on Open."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 40",
    "text" : "Whatever model you have open will close - you can only have one model open at a time in the model reader."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 41",
    "text" : "The Model Reader will only open .vmf files.  If someone has given you a file with extension .mdl it won't work.  You will need to ask them to save the model with extension .vmf."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 42",
    "text" : "What a model looks like"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 43",
    "text" : "Back to Overview"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 44",
    "text" : "Use the page up and page down keys to move through a model or, of the model has navigation buttons like this one does use those instead."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 45",
    "text" : "Making a Graph"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 46",
    "text" : "Once you have made a simulation you can make graph for any variable"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 47",
    "text" : "Double click on a variable name above and then click on a graph like icon at the left"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 48",
    "text" : "You can also select variable names by clicking on the Control Panel icon at the top and clicking on the Variable tab."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 49",
    "text" : "If you hold down the shift key and drag across a graph - the next time you make a graph it will be for a smaller time range.  Use the Time Axis button of the Control Panel to reset."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 50",
    "text" : "Back to Overview"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 51",
    "text" : "Printing and Copying"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 52",
    "text" : "To print what is on a view just delete any graphs, or push them to the background by clickin on the sketch, and then use File>Print"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 53",
    "text" : "To copy a view to the clipboard use Edit>Select all then Edit>Copy.  You can also select by dragging across an area"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 54",
    "text" : "To print or place a graph in the clipboard make the graph and then use File>Print or Edito>Copy (there are also icons on the graphs that do this)."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 55",
    "text" : "To show graphs you have placed in the background click on the Graph icon at the top (third from right)."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 56",
    "text" : "Back to Overview"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 57",
    "text" : "Vensim Info"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 58",
    "text" : "Vensim is available in a variety of configurations to meet your budget and performance needs.  For more information  contact us:"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 59",
    "text" : "Ventana Systems, Inc."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 60",
    "text" : "60 Jacob Gates Road"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 61",
    "text" : "Harvard MA 01451"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 62",
    "text" : "USA"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 63",
    "text" : "Sales 800 836 7461 (800 VENSIM1)"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 64",
    "text" : "International 508 651 0432"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 65",
    "text" : "Fax: 508 650 5422"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 66",
    "text" : "email:  vensim@vensim.com"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 67",
    "text" : "http://www.vensim.com"
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 68",
    "text" : "For technical support send email to reader@vensim.com.  We do not provide phone support for the Vensim Model Reader."
  }, {
    "name" : "Comment 69",
    "text" : "Back to Overview"
  } ],
